The paper deals with the wiretap channel, which is a topic in information theory (IT) and cryptography (CR). The paper proposes new metrics for security and applies cryptographic methods to produce explicit encryption schemes, which are topics in cryptography (CR) and complexity theory (CC). The paper also discusses the privacy implications of the wiretap channel, which is a topic in cybersecurity (CY) and security and privacy (SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.CR, followed by cs.CC, cs.CY, and cs.SI.
